[src:quantum-field-theory/feynman-diagram] In a path integral, the field Lagrangian, integrated over all possible field histories, defines the probability amplitude to go from one field configuration to another.
[src:quantum-field-theory/feynman-diagram] In order to make sense, the field theory must have a well-defined ground state, and the integral must be performed a little bit rotated into imaginary time, i.e. a Wick rotation.
[src:quantum-field-theory/feynman-diagram] The path integral formalism is completely equivalent to the canonical operator formalism above.
