[src:quantum-field-theory/feynman-diagram] In finite volume, the quantity ddk is not infinitesimal, but becomes the volume of a box made by neighboring Fourier modes, or (⁠2π/*V*⁠)*d* .
[src:quantum-field-theory/feynman-diagram] In terms of real and imaginary parts, the real part of *φ*(*k*) is an even function of k, while the imaginary part is odd.
