[src:quantum-field-theory/feynman-diagram] The form of the singularity can be understood from the canonical commutation relations to be a delta-function.
[src:quantum-field-theory/feynman-diagram] If the equations of motion are linear, the propagator will always be the reciprocal of the quadratic-form matrix that defines the free Lagrangian, since this gives the equations of motion.
[src:quantum-field-theory/feynman-diagram] This is also easy to see directly from the path integral.
